{"id":24369,"date":"2017-02-04T13:58:50","date_gmt":"2017-02-04T09:58:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=24369"},"modified":"2023-04-23T17:44:22","modified_gmt":"2023-04-23T13:44:22","slug":"ikhlaas-pure-deeds-allah-alone","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/02\/04\/ikhlaas-pure-deeds-allah-alone\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Sincerity: Make your deeds pure for Allah alone"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Dahhak ibn Qays reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Allah Almighty says: I am the best partner. Whoever associates another partner with Me, then I leave him to My partner.<\/strong>\u201d Then, the Prophet said, \u201c<strong>O people, make your deeds sincere for Allah Almighty. Verily, Allah does not accept any deed unless it is sincerely for Him. Do not say: This is for the sake of Allah and this is for the sake of my relatives. Verily, it was done for your relatives and none of it was for Allah. Do not say: This is for the sake of Allah and for your sake. Verily, it was done for their sake and none of it was for Allah.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Da\u0304raqut\u0323ni\u0304 111<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0636\u0651\u064e\u062d\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0643\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0633\u064d \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0641\u0650\u0647\u0652\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644